@startuml Interactive Command Flow
title "Interactive Command Architecture - Sequence Flow"

actor User
participant InputClassifier
participant CommandOrchestrator
participant CommandExecutor
participant TerminalUI
participant TokioRuntime

== Non-Interactive Command Flow ==

User -> InputClassifier: classify(input)
InputClassifier --> InputClassifier: Expand aliases
InputClassifier --> InputClassifier: Run 9-handler chain
activate InputClassifier
    note right of InputClassifier: 1. EmptyInputHandler\n2. HistoryExpansionHandler\n3. ShellBuiltinHandler\n4. PathCommandHandler\n5. KnownCommandHandler\n6. CommandSyntaxHandler\n7. TypoDetectionHandler\n8. NaturalLanguageHandler\n9. DefaultHandler

InputClassifier -> InputClassifier: Match handler logic
InputClassifier --> User: InputType::Command
deactivate InputClassifier

User -> CommandOrchestrator: handle_command(cmd, args, original_input)
CommandOrchestrator -> CommandOrchestrator: Check if requires_interactive()
CommandOrchestrator --> CommandOrchestrator: Case: Non-interactive\n(is_interactive() == false)

CommandOrchestrator -> CommandExecutor: execute(cmd, args, original_input)
activate CommandExecutor
    CommandExecutor --> CommandExecutor: Check INTERACTIVE_BLOCKED list
    note right of CommandExecutor: INTERACTIVE_BLOCKED:\nssh, python, node, gdb,\nmy sql, psql, mongo, etc.

    CommandExecutor --> CommandExecutor: Determine execution path:\n- Shell builtin? → sh -c\n- Shell operators? → sh -c\n- Regular command? → Direct execution

    CommandExecutor -> TokioRuntime: spawn async task\n(with 5min timeout)
    TokioRuntime --> CommandExecutor: CommandOutput\n{stdout, stderr, exit_code}
deactivate CommandExecutor

CommandExecutor --> CommandOrchestrator: CommandOutput
CommandOrchestrator -> CommandOrchestrator: Format and display output\nto TerminalState

CommandOrchestrator --> User: Output rendered to TUI

== Interactive Command Flow ==

User -> InputClassifier: classify(input)
InputClassifier --> User: InputType::Command{vim/top/nano/...}

User -> CommandOrchestrator: handle_command(cmd, args, ...)
CommandOrchestrator -> CommandOrchestrator: Check if requires_interactive()
CommandOrchestrator --> CommandOrchestrator: Case: Interactive\n(is_interactive() == true)

CommandOrchestrator -> CommandExecutor: execute_interactive(cmd, args, ui)
activate CommandExecutor
    CommandExecutor -> TerminalUI: suspend()
    activate TerminalUI
        TerminalUI -> TerminalUI: show_cursor()
        TerminalUI -> TerminalUI: flush() pending draws
        TerminalUI -> TerminalUI: execute(LeaveAlternateScreen)
        TerminalUI -> TerminalUI: disable_raw_mode()
        note right of TerminalUI: TUI is now suspended\nTerminal returns to normal state
    deactivate TerminalUI

    note right of CommandExecutor: Terminal is now in normal mode\nUser can interact with vim/less/top/etc.

    CommandExecutor -> TokioRuntime: spawn_blocking()\nRun actual command\n(unguarded process execution)
    TokioRuntime --> CommandExecutor: exit_status

    note right of CommandExecutor: RAII Guard ensures resume()\neven if command panics

    CommandExecutor -> TerminalUI: resume()
    activate TerminalUI
        TerminalUI -> TerminalUI: enable_raw_mode()
        TerminalUI -> TerminalUI: execute(EnterAlternateScreen)
        TerminalUI -> TerminalUI: clear()
        note right of TerminalUI: TUI is now resumed\nTerminal back in TUI mode
    deactivate TerminalUI
deactivate CommandExecutor

CommandExecutor --> CommandOrchestrator: CommandOutput\n{exit_code only,\nno stdout/stderr captured}

CommandOrchestrator -> CommandOrchestrator: Display completion message\n(success or exit code)

CommandOrchestrator --> User: Output rendered to TUI

@enduml
